#!N 
#!CDarkGreen #!N  #!Rall69 Changing the interactor style #!N #!EC In this 
example, you will change the interactor  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   style #!EF from "stepper" 
(as in the preceding example) to "slider." #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   
#!N #!N #!I30 #!N 1. Click on the scalar interactor  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Isosurface value #!EF if it is not already highlighted. #!N #!I30 
#!N 2. Click on  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Set Style #!EF in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Edit #!EF pull-down menu of the control panel. Another pull-down menu 
appears. #!N #!I30 #!N 3. Click on  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Slider #!EF . 
The interactor changes appearance. #!N #!I30 #!N 4. Select  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execute 
On Change #!EF as in the preceding example. #!N #!I30 #!N 
5. Using the left mouse button, drag the slider tab to 
the right or left to increase or decrease the isosurface value. 
#!N #!I30 #!N 6. Release the mouse button to generate an 
image corresponding to the new value. #!N #!I30 #!N 7. Select 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   End Execution #!EF in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execute #!EF pull-down menu. 
#!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic 
